value.0: Smilodon are more robustly built than any other cat, with particularly well-developed forelimbs and exceptionally long upper canine teeth. Their jaws are larger than those of other cats, and their upper canines are slender and fragile, adapted for precision killing. Their tail and ears are short to preserve body heat in the frozen tundra in which they usually dwell.
Frozen Wastes: Manticore of Ice Hide

Thylacoleo have very broad heads and immensely powerful jaws with large premolars adapted to cutting flesh and cracking bone.

Thylacoleo are distinguished by their front paws, with semi-opposable thumbs used for either climbing trees or gripping onto prey.

Mastodons are shorter than elephants but are heavily built. Although the skull is lower and flatter and of generally simpler construction than that of elephants, it is similar in appearance. The ears are smaller and not as prominent as those of elephants due to the cold climate they are native to.
OOC ring for all bosses, to protect against the more popular spells for instant death.

Like rhinoceros, elasmotherium have three working toes, but they have much longer legs, so they gallop like a horse - although much slower than one. They have a massive keratinous horn and a wooly coat covers their body. A unique feature to the elasmotherium is the presence of euhypsodonty (ever-growing or rootless molars).

Like other ground sloths, the giant sloth has a blunt snout, massive jaw, and large, peg-like teeth. The hind limbs are plantigrade (flat-footed), which along with its stout tail allow it to rear up into a semi-erect position to feed on tree leaves. The forelimbs have three highly developed claws that are used to strip leaves and tear off branches.

Titanis, also known as Terror Birds, have an elongated skull ending in a thin, hooked beak. They are large, flightless, carnivorous birds.  They have a short tail and round body, with long and powerful legs. They also have very robust toes - and one of the strongest middle toes known for a bird. They have very small, useless wings that are locked in against the body.

Elephant birds are large birds, with the largest reaching 3 meters (9.8 ft) tall in normal standing posture. They have vestigial wings, long legs and necks, and small heads relative to body size. They have straight, thick, conical beaks that are not hooked.

The main feature of glyptodons is their tortoise-like body armour that is made of bone segments called osteoderms or scutes. With this protection, they are armored like turtles, but unlike most turtles, can not withdraw their heads. Instead they have a bony cap on the top of their skull.

Macrauchenia patachonica live in cold and frozen regions. They resemble bulky camels without a hump, with a long neck like llamas and short trunks for their nose. The long neck enables the herbivore to reach leaves on plants and bushes.

Toxodon are perhaps one of the strangest animals ever discovered.  They have large muscular bodies and short stout legs with three functional toes; most of their body weight is borne by the central toe. Toxodon have a very unusual gait due to their peculiar proportions. They gallop to escape predators, but, like rhinos, they rely more on their size for protection against predators.
OOC ring for all bosses, to protect against the more popular spells for instant death.
